{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb41-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"15883"},"text":"§ 15883.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Maintaining and enhancing hydroelectricity incentives","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb42-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definition of qualified hydroelectric facility","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, the term “qualified hydroelectric facility” means a hydroelectric project that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb43-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb44-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/a/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is licensed by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb45-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/a/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is a hydroelectric project constructed, operated, or maintained pursuant to a permit or valid existing right-of-way granted prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1920-06-10"},"text":"June 10, 1920","children":[],"tail":", or a license granted pursuant to the Federal Power Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 791a","children":[],"tail":" et seq.);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb46-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is placed into service before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-11-15"},"text":"November 15, 2021","children":[],"tail":"; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb47-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb48-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/a/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is in compliance with all applicable Federal, Tribal, and State requirements; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb49-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/a/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" would be brought into compliance with the requirements described in subparagraph (A) as a result of the capital improvements carried out using an incentive payment under this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb4a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Incentive payments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall make incentive payments to the owners or operators of qualified hydroelectric facilities for capital improvements directly related to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb4b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" improving grid resiliency, including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb4c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" adapting more quickly to changing grid conditions;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb4d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" providing ancillary services (including black start capabilities, voltage support, and spinning reserves);","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb4e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" integrating other variable sources of electricity generation; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb4f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/1/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" managing accumulated reservoir sediments;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb50-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" improving dam safety to ensure acceptable performance under all loading conditions (including static, hydrologic, and seismic conditions), including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb51-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the maintenance or upgrade of spillways or other appurtenant structures;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb52-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" dam stability improvements, including erosion repair and enhanced seepage controls; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb53-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" upgrades or replacements of floodgates or natural infrastructure restoration or protection to improve flood risk reduction; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb54-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" environmental improvements, including—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb55-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/3/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" adding or improving safe and effective fish passage, including new or upgraded turbine technology, fish ladders, fishways, and all other associated technology, equipment, or other fish passage technology to a qualified hydroelectric facility;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb56-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/3/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" improving the quality of the water retained or released by a qualified hydroelectric facility;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb57-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/3/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" promoting downstream sediment transport processes and habitat maintenance; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb58-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/b/3/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" improving recreational access to the project vicinity, including roads, trails, boat ingress and egress, flows to improve recreation, and infrastructure that improves river recreation opportunity.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb59-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb5a-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/c/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Costs","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Incentive payments under this section shall not exceed 30 percent of the costs of the applicable capital improvement.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb5b-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/c/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Maximum amount","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Not more than 1 incentive payment may be made under this section with respect to capital improvements at a single qualified hydroelectric facility in any 1 fiscal year, the amount of which shall not exceed $5,000,000.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb5c-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s15883/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"There is authorized to be appropriated to the Secretary to carry out this section $553,600,000 for fiscal year 2022, to remain available until expended.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbfe6fb5d-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/58/tII/s247"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–58, title II, § 247","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58/dD/tIII/s40333/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58, div. D, title III, § 40333(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-11-15"},"text":"Nov. 15, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/135/1023"},"text":"135 Stat. 1023","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbfe6fb5e-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbfe6fb5f-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbfe6fb60-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Power Act, referred to in subsec. (a)(1)(B), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1920-06-10/ch285"},"text":"act June 10, 1920, ch. 285","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/41/1063"},"text":"41 Stat. 1063","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 12 (§ 791a et seq.) of Title 16, Conservation. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s791a"},"text":"section 791a of Title 16","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbfe6fb61-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"idbfe6fb62-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Wage Rate Requirements","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For provisions relating to rates of wages to be paid to laborers and mechanics on projects for construction, alteration, or repair work funded under div. D or an amendment by div. D of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/58"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–58","children":[],"tail":", including authority of Secretary of Labor, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s18851"},"text":"section 18851 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
